<i>[Episode 6]</i>

3
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:04,400
<i>Hello, the phone you dialed has been turned off.</i>

4
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:21,600
Come on, cheers!

5
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,100
<i>Cheers!</i>

6
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:32,900
A'Yuan, these are my best buddies.

7
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,100
I'm introducing them to you.

8
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:35,600
From now you, they're your friends too.

9
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:36,800
Isn't that great?

10
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,200
This is my little brother, A'Yuan, Xie Zhiyuan.

11
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,800
Hang out with him in the future.

12
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,700
Hi, A'Yuan.

13
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,000
Hello.

14
00:02:45,060 --> 00:02:47,440
A'Yuan. Yuan, do you know how to play 15-20?

15
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,800
No, I don't.

16
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,000
You don't know?

17
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,100
You guys can go ahead.

18
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:53,200
Okay, sure.

19
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,800
I'll play with whoever loses.

20
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,900
Why do you look so down?

21
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,200
Have some drinks.

22
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:03,600
My brother said I can only drink alcohol after I turn 18.

23
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,700
Kiddo, are you still letting your brother decide everything?

24
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:10,400
As a man, you have to be independent and stand your ground.

25
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,900
Got it?

26
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:13,200
Independence.

27
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,400
How am I supposed to be independent?

28
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,600
Well...

29
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:20,200
That means you're financially independent.

30
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,900
Don't you hate your brother's overbearingness?

31
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:24,800
That's because you aren't earning your own money. You have nothing to you.

32
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:29,100
Once you start making money, you'll have the confidence to do as you please.

33
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,400
You can be assertive.

34
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,200
Assertive?

35
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:36,000
Yes. I have to be assertive.

36
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:45,000
I think my brother's right.

37
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,800
Can you drink coconut milk?

38
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,000
Of course.

39
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:54,500
Madam, a bottle of coconut milk, please.

40
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:55,800
<i>Okay!</i>

41
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,500
Anyway, look on the bright side.

42
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,800
Right now, you're free.

43
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:05,400
Enjoy this sense of freedom.

44
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,100
Come on, finish your drinks.

45
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:11,400
Come on.

46
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,900
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

47
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,400
Why did you run away from home?

48
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:20,200
I shot to fame in my hometown.

49
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,200
Pay me ¥75 each.

50
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:34,000
You don't need to pay. It's my treat.

51
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,100
- No, I have to. It's just enough.
- There's really no need.

52
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:38,500
Take it.

53
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,400
Let's call it a day and gather some other time.

54
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,100
Okay. Bye-bye.

55
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:46,000
Bye-bye, kiddo.

56
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Bye-bye.

57
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,800
What's wrong?

58
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:55,600
Feeling homesick?

59
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,200
That's normal when you first leave home.

60
00:04:57,200 --> 00:05:00,100
Keep this in mind. Be independent.

61
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,400
Let's go.

62
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,300
Be independent.

63
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:15,800
I have to be independent. I need to get a job and make money.

64
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,000
I'm going to piss Xie Zhiyao off.

65
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,400
- Piss Xie Zhiyao off.
- Exactly.

66
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,400
He kicked my butt. He didn't give a damn about me.

67
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:22,400
He ignored me. I'll kill him with worry.

68
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:24,900
- Kill him with worry.
- Yes, kill him with worry.

69
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,600
Brother, I've made my decision.

70
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:31,500
From today on, I'll become a proper working adult.

71
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:35,100
- Follow me and you can be a proper working adult.
- Okay.

72
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:38,000
First, let me teach you how to say "welcome".

73
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,600
- You have to be passionate.
- Passionate.

74
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:41,400
It might not matter to the customers,

75
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,600
but the boss will see how enthusiastic you are.

76
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,800
- He'll be happy to see that.
- Happy?

77
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:46,100
- That's right.
- Brother, how should I say it?

78
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:52,200
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

79
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:54,000
You have to channel your breath into it.

80
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Welcome!

81
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Y-You have to pay attention to the rhythm.

82
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,200
Welcome!

83
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,800
Be enthusiastic and brave!

84
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:09,500
♪ <i>Be brave</i> ♪

85
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:18,200
♪ <i>This darkness is nothing but a misunderstanding</i> ♪

86
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:23,800
♪ <i>The twists and turns in life</i> ♪

87
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,000
♪ <i>make me</i> ♪

88
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,400
Have you found A'Yuan?

89
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:39,100
Nope. He ran away from home and took his bag with him.

90
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,400
He even brought a change of clothes.

91
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,400
I really didn't say a word.

92
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:45,600
That's not important right now.

93
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,300
Wait. This is extremely important.

94
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,100
I didn't expose him.

95
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:55,500
I swear. I've never even talked in my sleep.

96
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,200
If you say so.

97
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,200
What do you mean by that?

98
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,400
I did not.

99
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,000
Okay, fine.

100
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,200
Saying okay means you believe me, but "Okay, fine" means you doubt me

101
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,000
and you're just placating me.

102
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,300
Calm down. I wasn't implying anything.

103
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:15,200
Wait! Both of you can't wrong me like this.

104
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:18,800
The point is that we're the only two who know in this village.

105
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:21,200
We're the only two who know in this village.

106
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:24,800
I didn't say it. Well, perhaps you said it.

107
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,600
I'm cool with you interrupting my speech,

108
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:29,400
but why are you accusing me when I didn't even doubt you? Of course, I didn't say a word.

109
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:32,200
If we're the only possible culprits,

110
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,200
it's certainly not me.

111
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:36,200
It's not me either.

112
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:42,400
- This doesn't matter.
- This is very important.

113
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:45,200
Locating your brother is top priority now.

114
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,700
Why are you laughing?

115
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,400
You're so kind.

116
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,600
Weirdo.

117
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,600
I sent Guobao to the kindergarten

118
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,400
and ran into him at the mouth of the alley.

119
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,400
I just teased him

120
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:20,400
and asked him if he was skipping school because he crapped his pants.

121
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,200
He dashed off immediately.

122
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,200
Me... Me too.

123
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:34,200
He called me today and asked for Hongdou's number.

124
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:38,200
I asked him as a joke.

125
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,400
Well, who did you hear it from?

126
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:42,200
From my mom.

127
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:46,200
All the ladies in the warehouse know about this.

128
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:49,800
I guess Aunty E heard it from them, too.

129
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:52,800
So, we can't find out who started it.

130
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,500
Why are you looking into that? This doesn't matter.

131
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:57,000
It matters.

132
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,100
Neither of us uttered a word.

133
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,600
How the heck did word get out?

134
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,700
Why are you invested in how it spread?

135
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:04,200
Look for A'Yuan first.

136
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,600
You're to blame.

137
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,000
A joke?

138
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,000
How can you make a joke about this?

139
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,800
He's just a child.

140
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:15,500
At the age of 16 or 17, that's when a person's self-esteem is everything.

141
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:17,600
No matter how young a person is,

142
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,600
you can't make a joke about someone's humiliation.

143
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:26,000
You guys don't know a thing.

144
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:29,200
When Yang Guanjun was in junior high school, he went swimming in the reservoir.

145
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,400
His classmates hid his clothes.

146
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:34,100
When it was dark, he came back to the village butt-naked.

147
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:37,600
The ladies in the village thought he was a pervert and almost beat him up.

148
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,200
It's all in the past! Why are you dragging it out now?

149
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:41,200
I was just making a joke.

150
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:47,200
Well... Brother.

151
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:51,200
Do you think A'Yuan went back to Kunming?

152
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:54,700
He came here from Kunming because of this incident. Why would he go back?

153
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,000
Did you ask Uncle Siping?

154
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,400
I did.

155
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:01,200
You don't look the slightest bit anxious.

156
00:10:02,780 --> 00:10:04,600
Why would I be anxious?

157
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:07,800
He's all grown up and has money with him.

158
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,200
I may as well leave him be.

159
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,900
When he runs out of money, he'll come back himself.

160
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:15,000
You sure are taking this in your stride.

161
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,400
What if he steals and robs when he's out of money?

162
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,700
The law can punish him, then.

163
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,200
Xie Xiaoxia.

164
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:31,400
You're best buddies with him.

165
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:34,400
Didn't he tell you where he went?

166
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:37,700
Nope.

167
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,400
He told you to say that, didn't he?

168
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:46,000
No, Brother. I really don't know.

169
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:53,000
It's so much trouble to raise a child.

170
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,700
Why are these four children behaving so well today?

171
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,400
Take another bite.

172
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:26,400
These can't be bought from around here.

173
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,600
Come on.

174
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:33,100
Did he say something? What did he say?

175
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,200
He said he bought two tangerines

176
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,800
but they didn't taste sweet.

177
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,200
<i>[Office]</i>
We sell tons of tangerines.

178
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:43,200
We can't possibly peel everything to taste if they're sweet.

179
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,300
Exactly.

180
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:48,000
In older times, only the emperor in the palace

181
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,200
received such treatment.

182
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:54,800
The maids would always taste anything he ate first to test for poison.

183
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:57,800
So, the emperor ate leftovers from the maids?

184
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,600
Now that you say so, that sounds about right.

185
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,400
It's spoiled.

186
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,200
Chuchu.

187
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:06,200
Come and have a look.

188
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:09,000
Check if these tangerines were from us. He said three of them were spoiled.

189
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,800
How can she tell?

190
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:12,600
I can't really tell.

191
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,400
Aunty A'Gui, are you hanging out here again?

192
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:17,400
I came to chat with Aunty Feng.

193
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:19,200
We're working now.

194
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:22,000
I won't disrupt her work.

195
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,600
Manager, come and look at this.

196
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,200
Chuchu.

197
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,800
He says three of the tangerines are spoiled.

198
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,800
Were these bought from us?

199
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,200
Aren't these oranges?

200
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,900
I thought so, too.

201
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:35,700
But he's asking for compensation.

202
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:37,600
- Compensate him.
- No way.

203
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,700
Aunty Feng, just let this go.

204
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:41,900
We'll compensate all cases that are hard to discern.

205
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:44,300
But this is way out of line. Utterly unreasonable.

206
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:46,000
Aunty Feng, listen to me.

207
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,800
If you tell him that, he'll give us a bad review.

208
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,600
That'll harm our business.

209
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:52,200
Got it?

210
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:53,700
Fine.

211
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:55,100
Don't worry.

212
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:58,300
Manager, have you found A'Yuan?

213
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,600
Not yet.

214
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,600
It's been days.

215
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,500
Chairman Xie says he has money with him.

216
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:05,100
So, there's no need to worry.

217
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,000
A'Yao is wrong about this.

218
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:10,500
Why isn't he looking for his brother?

219
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:14,600
Children at that age can't tell good from bad.

220
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:17,600
If he hangs out with hooligans,

221
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,600
his life will be over.

222
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:22,000
They'll start with petty theft,

223
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:25,200
and then end up robbing others.

224
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:32,200
- No way.
- Why not?

225
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:36,400
He should've been spanked the moment he skipped school.

226
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:38,000
Look at him now.

227
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,500
His dad can't bear to hit him and sent him back to his hometown.

228
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:43,800
Now, his brother just lets him do as he pleases.

229
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:45,800
I just think we should find him first.

230
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:49,600
If he still doesn't behave, break his legs.

231
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:51,100
Let's see if he'll still rebel then.

232
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,400
All right, fine.

233
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:56,600
Aunty A'Gui. Can... Can you help us with the yams?

234
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,500
I'm here to hang out, not to work.

235
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:01,500
You're experienced. Come on, put on the gloves.

236
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,800
Okay, fine.

237
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:38,800
Hello. I've been waiting a long time for my porcino pancakes.

238
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:41,600
I'm sorry, we're a little crowded today. Please wait a minute.

239
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,000
All right, please hurry up.

240
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,300
Okay.

241
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,400
Let me help you. Which table is it?

242
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,700
The innermost tearoom.

243
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:55,400
Thank you.

244
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,400
Na Na.

245
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:00,900
Chairman Xie.

246
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,900
Why is Xu Hongdou serving food?

247
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:09,500
She came over to have a drink. She offered to help because I'm busy.

248
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:11,300
Are these the new books we ordered?

249
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:13,800
Yes. It's too heavy. I'm worried that you can't carry them,

250
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:15,200
so I brought them over.

251
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,800
I'll put them in the storage room first. Remember to unpack them.

252
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,300
Great.

253
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:25,400
♫ <i>A breeze wafts through some parts of the world</i> ♫

254
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:28,600
♫ <i>Hidden spots make my heart flutter</i> ♫

255
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:33,600
♫ <i>Whose dream will be fulfilled??</i> ♫

256
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:36,400
Na Na,

257
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:40,800
another latte and porcini pancake for Table 2.

258
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:43,300
- Do you have freebies?
- Freebies?

259
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:44,600
The guests at that table have been waiting for a long time.

260
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,000
They've already finished two glasses of water.

261
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:49,000
Do you have any snacks to offer them?

262
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:52,400
- I have some nuts and Mahjong cookies.
- Okay.

