284
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:11,100
♫ <i>Sometimes I find I fall in love</i> ♫

285
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:14,800
♫ <i>Make a little wish and pray</i> ♫

286
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:17,600
Na Na, I've put them in there.

287
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,400
Have you found A'Yuan?

288
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:22,100
Not yet. It's only been a few days.

289
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:23,800
Don't worry.

290
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:26,000
That's right. He's your brother, not mine.

291
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,600
Why should I be worried?

292
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:32,500
Is serving food part of a lobby manager's job?

293
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:34,800
A lobby manager's job is to provide good service.

294
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,600
I have to learn to do everything.

295
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:40,700
I thought you just needed to supervise your subordinates.

296
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:42,800
I need to manage everything.

297
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:45,000
You're pretty good with that.

298
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:53,800
I'm done here. You can get on with your work. I'll get going.

299
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:57,600
Chairman Xie, the light bulbs.

300
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:59,100
<i>Got it!</i>

301
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:02,600
Let me do it.

302
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,800
- I'll serve this first.
- Okay.

303
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:14,300
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much today.

304
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:15,800
This is one of our drinks, Encounter.

305
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:17,200
Have a taste.

306
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:20,000
It's a cold drink?

307
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:20,900
It's gorgeous.

308
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:23,400
Dark red roses taste completely different when cold brewed

309
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:25,700
and brewed with boiling water.

310
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:36,000
What a refreshing taste of roses.

311
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:39,900
Right? I think it's the taste of taking things slow.

312
00:18:39,900 --> 00:18:41,800
Taking things slow?

313
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:46,600
The taste of taking things slow. That's because an important ingredient is time.

314
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:52,300
Right now, many things are losing the ability to progress slowly.

315
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:55,000
Everything is speeding up.

316
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,300
Even people are treated as machines.

317
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,100
That's right.

318
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:03,200
I always described our hotel as a giant clock.

319
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:05,600
The employees are cogs within it.

320
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:09,000
We're pressed for time and racing against time.

321
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:13,400
In a competition against time,

322
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,800
humans will always lose.

323
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,000
You're right.

324
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:24,000
♫ <i>The raindrops from the roof drip into my eyes quietly</i> ♫

325
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:29,400
♫ <i>The world is like a quiet island</i> ♫

326
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:38,400
♫ <i>The reflection of clouds, the changing moon,
and the starry sky</i> ♫

327
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:42,800
<i>Hongdou, what do you think we'll look like when we grow old?</i>

328
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:49,100
♫ <i>The light and shadows of the seasons</i> ♫

329
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:53,800
♫ <i> I've seen the meteor that lights up the night sky</i> ♫

330
00:19:53,800 --> 00:20:00,000
♫ <i>When the wind rises, the sky will be cloudless</i> ♫

331
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:05,200
♫ <i>I'll head to a windy place to meet you</i> ♫

332
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,400
- Brother A'Yao.
- Yang Xu.

333
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,000
Has your brother come home?

334
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,200
Nope.

335
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,400
Why don't you go find him?

336
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:14,900
There's no need for that. He'll come back when he's bored.

337
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:18,000
Children at that age aren't sensible.

338
00:20:19,100 --> 00:20:21,400
How's your business?

339
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:24,200
There are more drivers than tourists. We've got too few customers.

340
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:26,900
I'm planning to quit, take out a loan, and buy a car.

341
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:28,600
Buy a car?

342
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:31,200
My cousin and his family are living in Kunming. I've asked him about it.

343
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:33,800
With a car, I'll work as a driver there, and my wife can do housekeeping.

344
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,500
When we've earned some money, we'll find a school and bring our child over.

345
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:40,200
Doesn't that mean Tuotuo has to live with his grandparents?

346
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:41,800
Yeah. There's nothing we can do.

347
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:43,600
We can't make any money.

348
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:45,200
Things will get better.

349
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:47,400
The government is developing the tourism industry—

350
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,700
Who knows what will happen?

351
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:54,200
We'll come back when things get better.

352
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,200
Right now, the family needs to be fed.

353
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,600
Tuotuo's going to attend elementary school soon.

354
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,700
We can't always live off our farmland.

355
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:03,200
I'll go look for customers.

356
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,200
Xiao Qin.

357
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:20,300
Get me two light bulbs. 12 watts, yellow light.

358
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:22,000
Gotcha.

359
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:28,200
I heard that A'Yuan is playing truant because he had a stomach ache

360
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:29,500
and pooped on his teacher's pants.

361
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:32,200
How did he do that?

362
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,600
Who did you hear that from?

363
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:34,800
My mom.

364
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:36,500
She heard it from someone else.

365
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:39,600
Someone even said that he pooped at the school gates. I don't buy that.

366
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:42,000
So, you believe that he pooped on his teacher's pants?

367
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,800
Well, who did he poop on?

368
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:46,500
He's the one with the stomach ache. What do you think?

369
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:50,400
I don't know. I asked you on WeChat, but you ignored my message.

370
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:51,600
Here you go.

371
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:54,900
Tell me first. Who did he poop on?

372
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,600
Give it to me.

373
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,400
I want to have dinner at your place tonight.

374
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:02,800
Your braised beef with wine is delicious.

375
00:22:02,800 --> 00:22:06,700
Your dad came to see me yesterday and talked about you.

376
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,600
Did he offer my hand in marriage?

377
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:11,600
He wants me to persuade you to become an apprentice at the embroidery workshop.

378
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:13,600
I'm not going. Even you can't convince me to go.

379
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:16,000
Tell him to give up.

380
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,580
Your dad just wants you to learn a trade.

381
00:22:19,580 --> 00:22:22,340
When I was a child, I watched my granny embroider all day long.

382
00:22:22,340 --> 00:22:23,940
A piece of clothing took her six months.

383
00:22:23,940 --> 00:22:26,600
Now that she's old, her back is hunched and she's going blind.

384
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:28,839
Each piece barely brings in any money.

385
00:22:28,839 --> 00:22:30,220
I'm not going there.

386
00:22:30,220 --> 00:22:33,079
- You—
- Two light bulbs for ¥40. Payment through WeChat, right?

387
00:22:33,079 --> 00:22:34,820
I won't profit off you.

388
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:49,280
Okay, give it a try.

389
00:22:51,860 --> 00:22:54,060
Sorry, I came over to change it so late in the night.

390
00:22:54,060 --> 00:22:56,220
It's fine. I haven't started cooking yet.

391
00:22:56,220 --> 00:22:58,539
- Where else needs to be fixed?
- Oh, the terrace.

392
00:22:58,539 --> 00:23:00,800
It's been down for days. Na Na is waiting for you upstairs.

393
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,719
- Okay, I'll go check it.
- Thank you.

394
00:23:02,719 --> 00:23:04,340
You're welcome.

395
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,799
I bought tomatoes.

396
00:23:07,799 --> 00:23:09,800
Let's have egg noodles with tomato omelette tonight.

397
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:12,000
It's easy to cook.

398
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,700
Hongdou, what are you looking at?

399
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:18,320
Hasn't Chairman Xie gone to look for his brother at all?

400
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:20,380
He probably doesn't know where to start looking.

401
00:23:20,380 --> 00:23:22,660
I don't think he cares either.

402
00:23:22,660 --> 00:23:24,739
Perhaps he really isn't worried.

403
00:23:24,740 --> 00:23:28,820
Na Na told me that Chairman Xie and his brother don't share the same mother.

404
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,820
When Chairman Xie was very young,

405
00:23:31,820 --> 00:23:35,840
his parents left him here and went to work in Kunming.

406
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:38,760
His mother passed away due to illness.

407
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:41,079
After a few years, his dad remarried and had his brother.

408
00:23:41,079 --> 00:23:44,360
They've never lived together.

409
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:48,100
People need to spend time together to forge a bond.

410
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:52,140
<i>Deqing is like an old peacock.</i>

411
00:23:52,140 --> 00:23:55,179
He's always putting his feathers on display wherever he goes.

412
00:23:55,180 --> 00:23:58,140
He's been like this since he was younger.

413
00:23:58,140 --> 00:23:59,980
Hongdou!

414
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:01,360
Is A'Yao with you?

415
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:04,600
A'Yao's changing the light bulbs.

416
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:06,700
A'Yao.

417
00:24:06,700 --> 00:24:09,360
Come down. We need to talk to you.

418
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:11,340
<i>Wait for me to change the light bulb. I won't take long.</i>

419
00:24:11,340 --> 00:24:14,100
Let's wait for him to finish.

420
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:19,499
Hongdou, let me introduce Aunty Feng to you.

421
00:24:19,499 --> 00:24:21,300
Aunty Feng.

422
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:23,139
Come on, let's wait for him.

423
00:24:23,139 --> 00:24:25,620
Have a seat. I'll make you some tea.

424
00:24:25,620 --> 00:24:27,499
There's no need. I'm not thirsty.

425
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:30,640
So what if you aren't? I'm thirsty.

426
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:33,219
- Thanks, Hongdou.
- You're welcome.

427
00:24:33,219 --> 00:24:37,319
How can A'Yao be in the mood to be changing light bulbs?

428
00:24:37,319 --> 00:24:42,200
Stop being so impatient. You're like a cockerel about to explode.

429
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:44,179
Why are Aunty Baoping and the rest here?

430
00:24:44,180 --> 00:24:46,720
I don't know. They said they need to talk to Chairman Xie.

431
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:49,360
Are these shared cups?

432
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:51,400
Mr. Ma bought this for us to drink.

433
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:53,280
Use it to make tea.

434
00:24:54,620 --> 00:24:56,500
Aunty Feng looks really stern.

435
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:58,400
Who is she?

436
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:01,960
She works in Chairman Xie's web store with Aunty Baoping.

437
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,560
Aunty Baoping is responsible for deliveries.

438
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:05,520
Aunty Feng is in charge of customer service.

439
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:07,100
Chiarman Xie's web store?

440
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:09,200
Isn't that Xiaochun's shop?

441
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:14,320
Chairman Xie hired Xiaochun as a manager.

442
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:17,160
So, Xiaochun only owns the cafe.

443
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:20,119
Didn't I say that Xiaochun is just a manager?

444
00:25:20,119 --> 00:25:21,380
Everyone calls him Chairman Xie.

445
00:25:21,380 --> 00:25:22,779
Even you do so sometimes.

446
00:25:22,780 --> 00:25:25,239
That's because he's the owner of the horse ranch.

447
00:25:25,239 --> 00:25:27,520
He owns the horse ranch.

448
00:25:27,520 --> 00:25:31,660
He also owns the embroidery workshop, the tie-dye workshop, and this courtyard.

449
00:25:32,620 --> 00:25:36,380
You're cooped up indoors all day. Why do you know so much?

450
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:43,080
When I'm cooking, Na Na always tells me about the village's gossip.

451
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:45,700
There's gossip here?

452
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:47,560
Tons of it.

453
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:51,280
Gossip...

454
00:25:52,220 --> 00:25:53,720
- Have some fruit.
- Hongdou.

455
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:56,100
- There's fruit?
- Hongdou, sit here.

456
00:25:56,100 --> 00:25:57,820
- Sit over here.
- Thank you.

457
00:25:57,820 --> 00:26:00,459
I don't believe she's already 30.

458
00:26:00,460 --> 00:26:03,180
I am. I'm two years older than Xiaochun.

459
00:26:03,180 --> 00:26:05,659
You look too young to be 30.

460
00:26:05,659 --> 00:26:07,339
When we were young,

461
00:26:07,340 --> 00:26:11,700
we had to pick mushrooms on Cang Mountain and fish in Erhai Lake.

462
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:15,319
We braved the sun and rain without applying any cream.

463
00:26:15,319 --> 00:26:17,339
So, we all look old.

464
00:26:17,340 --> 00:26:20,039
Xiao Xi is different.

465
00:26:20,039 --> 00:26:23,039
She's also 30, but her skin is so tender.

466
00:26:23,039 --> 00:26:25,200
You look just like her.

467
00:26:27,220 --> 00:26:28,439
What was that?

468
00:26:28,439 --> 00:26:30,200
What about that?

469
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:33,640
You humphed when I said Hongdou looks like Xiao Xi.

470
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:35,379
What's wrong with Xiao Xi?

471
00:26:35,380 --> 00:26:38,540
- Xiao Xi is great.
- Of course.

472
00:26:38,540 --> 00:26:40,920
Look at her hand.

473
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:42,559
So delicate.

474
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:44,900
I'm sure she hasn't done any physical labor.

475
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:47,840
How nice.

476
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:49,760
Her fingers are so aligned.

477
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:52,060
That means wealth will stay with you.

478
00:26:52,060 --> 00:26:54,019
Baoping is amazing at palm reading.

479
00:26:54,020 --> 00:26:56,220
She studied Dayang's palm

480
00:26:56,220 --> 00:26:58,639
and said he'll be the top scholar.

481
00:26:58,639 --> 00:27:01,060
Sure enough, he's doing well in life.

482
00:27:01,060 --> 00:27:03,260
What else?

483
00:27:03,260 --> 00:27:04,900
Your love line is promising, too.

484
00:27:04,900 --> 00:27:06,680
That's good.

485
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:10,460
She's clearly a blessed girl.

486
00:27:10,460 --> 00:27:12,579
You only say nice things.

487
00:27:12,579 --> 00:27:14,160
What else is she supposed to say?

488
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:16,480
Show your hand to Baoping.

489
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:17,899
What for?

490
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:21,060
In this day and age, I don't believe such things.

491
00:27:21,060 --> 00:27:24,099
- I'm coming.
- Come and have seat.

492
00:27:24,099 --> 00:27:25,300
Hold on.

493
00:27:25,300 --> 00:27:28,680
What's so urgent? Isn't a call more convenient?

494
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:30,200
We have to say it to your face.

495
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:33,760
Don't find us annoying.

496
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:36,880
We have to lay things out today.

497
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:39,060
-You guys can chat. I'll...
- Hongdou, sit down.

498
00:27:39,060 --> 00:27:41,080
Sit down. We're going to talk about A'Yuan.

499
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:42,859
You should stay and listen.

500
00:27:42,860 --> 00:27:44,940
Have some strawberries.

501
00:27:44,940 --> 00:27:47,080
Everyone has been asking me about this lately.

502
00:27:47,080 --> 00:27:49,200
My throat is parched from explaining.

503
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:51,400
He's a grown man. What could possibly happen to him?

504
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:53,460
I know what I'm doing, all right?

505
00:27:53,460 --> 00:27:55,400
Like hell you do.

506
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:57,819
A'Yuan is still a child.

507
00:27:57,820 --> 00:28:00,980
He doesn't know he's in danger, and we don't know what he's doing.

508
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:04,620
He's been away for ages, but you aren't even searching for him.

509
00:28:04,620 --> 00:28:06,539
He probably doesn't know where to start looking.

510
00:28:06,540 --> 00:28:09,320
Even if he's at a loss, he should try searching.

511
00:28:09,320 --> 00:28:12,760
If he doesn't even try, do you know what the villagers will say?

512
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:14,860
"They don't even share the same mother anyway."

513
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:17,219
"A'Yao just doesn't care."

514
00:28:17,220 --> 00:28:20,660
Just ignore their nonsense.

515
00:28:20,660 --> 00:28:23,540
We can ignore their nonsense,

